  catalogueCvaTitle: 'CVA',
  catalogueCvaCapacityText: 'Support the host National Society to carry out cash feasibility, market assessment, selection and contracting of Financial Services Provider, cash disbursements, data management and reporting via the deployment of a Cash Coordinator, Cash Officer and Cash IM officer.\n\nCash Coordinator, Cash Officer and Cash IM Officer profiles are deployed through the roster of trained professionals maintained by the IFRC Geneva Cash team.',
  catalogueCvaEmergencyListItem1: 'Can support the host National Society to carry out cash feasibility, market assessment, selection and contracting of Financial Services Provider, cash disbursements, data management and reporting.',
  catalogueCvaEmergencyListItem2: 'Can carry out advocacy for use of cash as response option.',
  catalogueCvaEmergencyListItem3: 'Can support the sectors in designing interventions with cash as response option.',
  catalogueCvaEmergencyListItem4: 'Representation of Movement in external working groups.',
  catalogueCvaDesignedText: 'Cash Coordinator, Cash Officer and Cash IM Officer profiles support the following activities:',
  catalogueCvaDesignedAssesment: 'Data Collection Plan, 4Ws management, Priority Needs Calculation, Assessment Findings Consolidation.',
  catalogueCvaDesignedResponse: 'Response Options Weighting, Transfer Value Calculation, Vulnerability & Hazard Mapping, Priority Needs Calculation, Targeting Data Analysis (Geographic, Vulnerability Criteria).',
  catalogueCvaDesignedSetup: 'CEA Infographics, People Targeted Data Processing & Protection, Distribution/Encashment Planning Analysis, Distribution Reporting & Progress Mapping, Complaint & Feedback Mechanism Database.',
  catalogueCvaDesignedMonitoring: 'Exit Survey Data Collection & Analysis, PDM Data Collection & Analysis, Price Market Data Collection, Case Studies, Lessons Learned, Final Documentation.',
  catalogueCvaPersonnelTotal: '1+ people',
  catalogueCvaPersonnelCompoistion1: 'Cash Coordinator x 1 for cash feasibility, advocacy, mainstreaming cash into sectoral activities.',
  catalogueCvaPersonnelCompoistion2: 'Cash Officer x 1 for implementation. More Cash Officers can be deployed based on the geographical needs.',
  catalogueCvaPersonnelCompoistion3: 'Cash IM Officer x 1 for data management, support in reporting, visualization and decision making.',
  catalogueCvaStandardCompText: 'Cash in Emergencies toolkit, with tools, templates and guidelines available for implementation of any CVA intervention.',
  catalogueCvaSpecifiationCost: 'HR only, depends upon the assignment.',
  catalogueCvaSpecifiationNationalSocieties: 'In the last years, many National Societies have enhanced their capacity and have contributed to CVA deployments.',
  catalogueCommunityEngagementTitle: 'Community Engagement and Accountability',
  catalogueCommunityEngagementCapacityText: 'Provision of technical expertise to enhance the impact, reach and efficiency of emergency response operations through the integration and coordination of community engagement and accountability activities and approaches. This includes participatory approaches, feedback systems, risk communication/behaviour change communication (in closed collaboration with health promotion delegates) and evidence-based advocacy.',
  catalogueCommunityEngagementEmergencyText: 'Provide support in response operations through the CEA roster of trained professionals from the IFRC and National Societies.\n\nFlexible team (Tier 1 and 2) that can be adapted to the specific needs of a response (which could focus more on accountability issues or risk communication and community engagement as it is the case of epidemics), depending of needs and capacity of the HNS/operation.',
  catalogueCommunityEngagementDesignedListItem1: 'Provide technical guidance and advice to guide community engagement assessments, as part of intersectoral assessment work towards collecting information and feedback needs and channels as well as insights on socio-cultural and contextual factors that can inform planning and guide community engagement efforts.',
  catalogueCommunityEngagementDesignedListItem2: 'Supports the planning, rolling out and adaptation of CEA tools, methodologies, trainings and activities based on the needs assessment and suitable to the local context and cultural practices.',
  catalogueCommunityEngagementDesignedListItem3: 'Supports and ensures use across operations teams of the most relevant social sciences research, impact surveys and perception data (including social-cultural data, sources of vulnerabilities, community structures and power dynamics) to support the design of comprehensive and evidence-based community engagement approaches in the operations.',
  catalogueCommunityEngagementDesignedListItem4: 'Supports the setting up/strengthening of appropriate feedback methods and systems to gain a deeper understanding of the community feedback, including perceptions, beliefs, rumours and complaints. Ensures feedback, community perceptions and insights are regularly analysed and shared with key operation teams and decision makers to inform action.',
  catalogueCommunityEngagementDesignedListItem5: 'Designs and facilitates the training of staff and volunteers on essential CEA aspects, including on the code of conduct, good communication skills, dealing with complaints and ensuring that feedback is acted upon.',
  catalogueCommunityEngagementPersonnelTotal: 'Generally 2 people.',
  catalogueCommunityEngagementPersonnelCompoistion: 'Tier 1 Officer, and Tier 2 Coordinator.',
  catalogueCert1Title: 'Communications Emergency Response Tool (CERT) 1',
  catalogueCert1CapacityText: 'Rapid deployment of communications professionals at the outset of and during a disaster or emergency can support IFRC and its members to:',
  catalogueCert1CapacityListItem1: 'Shape the public story and seize the immediate media opportunity in the first 24-72 hours following an emergency (or 24-36 hours prior to an imminent disaster).',
  catalogueCert1CapacityListItem2: 'Raise funds for appeals.',
  catalogueCert1CapacityListItem3: 'Protect against reputational criticisms of inaction that invariably follow any emergency response.',
  catalogueCert1CapacityListItem4: 'Provide first-hand information and analysis on disaster and crisis situations (including for international media and content generation).',
  catalogueCert1CapacityListItem5: 'Communication with affected communities – share life-saving information and support delivery of better services.',
  catalogueCert1CapacityListItem6: 'Influence partners and decision makers - advocacy on behalf of affected communities.',
  catalogueCert1CapacityListItem7: 'Profile the work of the Red Cross and Red Crescent - create a better understanding of what we do, gain trust and generate more support.',
  catalogueCert1EmergencyText: 'Rapid deployment (within 36 hours upon receiving a deployment request) of suitable and relevant role profile(s) to provide field-based communications support to a small to medium scale emergency response operations in a low to moderate complexity context, and with high level of attention from international media and global public interest.\n\nThe CERT1 team will provide technical support and advice to the operations, host National Society and member National Societies on the ground with the aim of highlighting the needs of affected people, the work of the Red Cross Red Crescent in responding to these needs, and advocating for increased action to address vulnerabilities and unmet humanitarian needs. The focus of this CERT team will be on:',
  catalogueCert1EmergencyListItem1: 'Communications capacity and needs assessment, planning and implementing communications strategies.',
